name: Chicago Pump Co. v. Infilco, Inc.
name_abbreviation: Chicago Pump Co. v. Infilco, Inc.

court.name: United States Court of Customs and Patent Appeals

parties: Chicago Pump Co. v. Infilco, Inc.

opinions.text: Trademark for a machine intended to be interposed in and across a sewage stream and adapted to intercept and screen solids carried by the stream and permit the sewage liquor and the unscreened small solids to pass therethrough.

casebody.head_matter:
January 10, 1958
Chicago Pump Co. v. Infilco, Inc.
(No. 6335).
